wikipedia_page.main: Duncan Victor Norbury (3 August 1887 – 23 October 1972) was an English all-round sportsman, who played football for Southampton and first-class cricket for Hampshire and Lancashire.

response: *Victor Norbury (1887 – 1972), Hampshire and Lancashire cricketer, and Southampton F.C. footballer

*Professional Bowlers with over 100 wickets in a season - Billy Mitchell - 1902, Freddie Bull - 1907, Victor Norbury - 1912, 1913, Bill Merritt - 1934, 1935, Bruce Dooland - 1949, Fazal Mahmood - 1959, Ray Strauss - 1960, Paul Reiffel - 1990, Claude Henderson - 1999

Arthur Dawson batted for Rishton from 1901 to 1912,Arthur Dawson Rishton matches  and opened for East Lancs. between 1913 and 1921.Arthur Dawson East Lancs. matches On many occasions he was batting opposite Victor Norbury, and one of their partnershipsColne v East Lancs. 26 July 1919 became an East Lancs. record not bettered until the 1960s. Both players featured strongly in the 1919 League win, East Lancs. League Matches in 1919 scoring over 45% of the total runs between them in roughly equal measure.
His brother-in-law was Victor Norbury, who also played cricket for Hampshire and football for Southampton.
